00:38:17,631 --> 00:38:18,832
It's his whole life.

764
00:38:18,866 --> 00:38:21,234
Everything that happened
is in that line.

765
00:38:21,268 --> 00:38:23,236
What are you gonna do
with your line now, Puckerman?

766
00:38:23,270 --> 00:38:25,305
I'm gonna make a man of myself.

767
00:38:25,339 --> 00:38:27,474
(sighs)

768
00:38:27,508 --> 00:38:29,709
Figured if I don't have Finn,
I need an army to help me.

769
00:38:29,710 --> 00:38:31,211
Are you serious? The army?

770
00:38:31,245 --> 00:38:32,479
Air Force, actually.

771
00:38:32,513 --> 00:38:34,848
Thought maybe I could be
a top gun.

772
00:38:34,882 --> 00:38:37,383
I think they were actually
Naval aviators in that movie.

773
00:38:39,553 --> 00:38:41,354
You know, if Finn was around,

774
00:38:41,388 --> 00:38:43,723
I'd just keep letting him
point me in the right direction.

775
00:38:45,359 --> 00:38:46,960
Now...

776
00:38:46,994 --> 00:38:49,262
it's up to me
to figure it all out.

777
00:38:49,296 --> 00:38:51,564
I'm proud of you.

778
00:38:51,599 --> 00:38:53,233
You know?

779
00:38:53,267 --> 00:38:55,001
Just don't get shot, okay?

780
00:38:55,035 --> 00:38:56,936
Thanks, Coach.

781
00:38:56,971 --> 00:38:59,639
(grunts affectionately)

782
00:38:59,673 --> 00:39:01,674
(sighs)

783
00:39:03,611 --> 00:39:05,011
Keep watering that tree.

784
00:39:05,045 --> 00:39:06,779
You got it.

785
00:39:06,814 --> 00:39:08,781
Have a good line.

786
00:39:08,816 --> 00:39:10,884
(engine starts)

787
00:39:23,378 --> 00:39:25,412
Hey, Mr. Shue.

788
00:39:25,447 --> 00:39:27,314
Hey, Rachel.

789
00:39:27,349 --> 00:39:29,817
I get flashbacks when you walk
in here and say that.

790
00:39:29,851 --> 00:39:31,519
Good ones.

791
00:39:31,553 --> 00:39:33,187
How are you doing?

792
00:39:33,221 --> 00:39:35,389
Everyone keeps asking me that.

793
00:39:35,423 --> 00:39:37,725
Well, from what I hear,
you've been a rock for everyone,

794
00:39:37,759 --> 00:39:39,827
so I know that that means

795
00:39:39,861 --> 00:39:41,896
that sometimes you don't get
to grieve yourself.

796
00:39:41,930 --> 00:39:43,731
I'm okay.

797
00:39:43,765 --> 00:39:46,233
I mean, I'm...

798
00:39:46,268 --> 00:39:47,434
I'm really not okay,

799
00:39:47,469 --> 00:39:49,503
but, uh, yeah,

800
00:39:49,538 --> 00:39:51,105
I'm-I'm okay.

801
00:39:51,139 --> 00:39:54,375
More importantly, how are you?

802
00:39:58,313 --> 00:40:01,015
I have no idea.

803
00:40:01,049 --> 00:40:03,551
(sighs)

804
00:40:03,585 --> 00:40:05,786
I talk to him a lot.

805
00:40:07,756 --> 00:40:09,490
I can still see his face

806
00:40:09,524 --> 00:40:12,793
and can hear his voice
so clearly.

807
00:40:12,827 --> 00:40:15,796
Do you think
that I'll ever forget it?

808
00:40:17,999 --> 00:40:20,601
'Cause I'm afraid
that one day, I will.

809
00:40:20,635 --> 00:40:22,536
What do you talk to him about?

810
00:40:22,571 --> 00:40:24,204
Anything.

811
00:40:24,239 --> 00:40:26,273
I mean, when we were dating,
it was, you know,

812
00:40:26,308 --> 00:40:27,741
pretty much me talking
all the time

813
00:40:27,776 --> 00:40:29,443
and him just pretending
to listen,

814
00:40:29,477 --> 00:40:30,678
so it's not really
that different.

815
00:40:30,712 --> 00:40:31,745
(chuckles)

816
00:40:31,780 --> 00:40:34,114
I had it all planned out.

817
00:40:34,149 --> 00:40:36,984
(crying)

818
00:40:37,018 --> 00:40:40,554
I was gonna make it big
on Broadway

819
00:40:40,589 --> 00:40:44,191
and maybe do
a Woody Allen movie.

820
00:40:44,225 --> 00:40:46,794
And then when we were ready,

821
00:40:46,828 --> 00:40:49,930
I would just...

822
00:40:49,965 --> 00:40:52,666
come back,
and he'd be teaching here,

823
00:40:52,701 --> 00:40:54,768
and I'd walk
through those doors,

824
00:40:54,803 --> 00:40:56,470
and I would just say,
"I'm home."

825
00:40:58,540 --> 00:41:00,207
And then we would live

826
00:41:00,241 --> 00:41:02,409
happily ever after.

827
00:41:02,444 --> 00:41:05,613
It's a good plan.

828
00:41:05,647 --> 00:41:07,615
Did you tell him?

829
00:41:07,649 --> 00:41:08,949
I didn't have to.

830
00:41:08,984 --> 00:41:10,884
He knew.

831
00:41:10,919 --> 00:41:13,020
And...

832
00:41:13,054 --> 00:41:14,989
now what?

833
00:41:15,023 --> 00:41:16,991
I don't know.

834
00:41:17,025 --> 00:41:18,258
Something different.

835
00:41:18,293 --> 00:41:19,960
Maybe something better.

836
00:41:19,995 --> 00:41:22,863
I just... I don't think
that that's possible.

837
00:41:24,299 --> 00:41:26,300
He was my person.

838
00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:33,540
But thank you so much
for doing this.

839
00:41:33,575 --> 00:41:36,777
I felt like I didn't know

840
00:41:36,811 --> 00:41:38,545
if I would be able
to sing again,

841
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:42,016
but now I know that I can.

842
00:41:43,385 --> 00:41:46,020
And I know that there have been
a lot of memorials for him,

843
00:41:46,054 --> 00:41:48,422
but I had this made,

844
00:41:48,456 --> 00:41:50,958
and I was hoping
that we could hang it in here.

845
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:57,197
(sighs)

846
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,100
Did he really say that?

847
00:42:00,135 --> 00:42:01,769
(both chuckling)

848
00:42:01,803 --> 00:42:03,404
He was smart, just, you know,

849
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:05,639
in an... in an untraditional
kind of way.

850
00:42:05,674 --> 00:42:06,874
(chuckles)

851
00:42:08,343 --> 00:42:11,078
Come on, let's... let's
hang it right over there.

852
00:42:35,336 --> 00:42:37,337
(sighs)

853
00:42:57,992 --> 00:42:59,927
♪

854
